<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="P1" checkit-title="Sample Spaces">
    <statement>
        <p>
Suppose you have 3 spinners that have 2, 6, and 2 equally sized spaces, respectively. Write out the sample space that corresponds to this situation. What is the probability that the sum of the spinner results is less than 6?
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
        The sample space is
        </p>
        <me>
\begin{array} {llllllllllll} \{(1,1,1), &amp; (1,1,2), &amp; (1,2,1), &amp; (1,2,2), &amp; (1,3,1), &amp; (1,3,2), &amp; (1,4,1), &amp; (1,4,2), &amp; (1,5,1), &amp; (1,5,2), &amp; (1,6,1), &amp; (1,6,2), \\ (2,1,1), &amp; (2,1,2), &amp; (2,2,1), &amp; (2,2,2), &amp; (2,3,1), &amp; (2,3,2), &amp; (2,4,1), &amp; (2,4,2), &amp; (2,5,1), &amp; (2,5,2), &amp; (2,6,1), &amp; (2,6,2) \}\end{array}
        </me>
        <p>
        The probability is 8/24.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
